8:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":["$","section",null,{"className":"space-y-4 py-12 sm:py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-3","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-semibold text-zinc-50 mt-6 mb-6","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-crimson)"},"children":"Background"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300 whitespace-pre-line max-w-[900px]","children":["Clay is a tool developed for Google allowing Project Executives to more easily plan and develop office renovation projects in-house, and then seamlessly hand-off to their external design teams. As a sort in between spreadsheets and the drawing board of CAD or Revit, there are multiple stages a project can move through, and multiple types of studies a user can create for a project. Clay home is where a user can find metadata about these studies and access their desired work. Clay is an amalgamation of a series of previously disparate applications that are all accomplishing similar work in parallel. Clay is intended to help a variety of users (Project Executives, Project Analysts, architects, interior designers, etc) streamline their collaborative process together."]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-2 pt-6","children":[["$","$Le",null,{"src":"/images/clay_combined.png","alt":"Multiple apps that are being combined into Clay","lightbox":true}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-zinc-400","children":"Multiple apps that are being combined into Clay"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"border-t border-white/10","children":["$","section",null,{"className":"space-y-4 py-12 sm:py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-3","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-semibold text-zinc-50 mt-6 mb-6","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-crimson)"},"children":"Initial discovery"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300 whitespace-pre-line max-w-[900px]","children":["The first step for the team was to understand the underlying structure and connections between different studies, and establish boundaries between them. Some of the app structure is based off of pre-existing work, and some new, so there was a lot of discovery involved in how a user should move through the different Clay experiences. I worked very closely with product and engineering in this exploration process."]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-2 pt-6","children":[["$","$Le",null,{"src":"/images/clay_home.gif","alt":"Boundaries between services, tools, and users","lightbox":true}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-zinc-400","children":"Boundaries between services, tools, and users"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"border-t border-white/10","children":["$","section",null,{"className":"space-y-4 py-12 sm:py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-3","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-semibold text-zinc-50 mt-6 mb-6","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-crimson)"},"children":"Approach"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300 whitespace-pre-line max-w-[900px]","children":["The primary goals for this design was to provide an intuitive platform where new users could easily understand how and what they could access, and existing users could quickly find where they left off. As we got further into understanding the boundaries between different states within Clay, it became clear that Google Drive would be a very helpful precedent. Like Drive, Clay has a variety of types of work a user can accomplish. Unlike Drive, the different \"files\" are interlinked and interdependent."]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-2 pt-6","children":[["$","$Le",null,{"src":"/images/clay_project.png","alt":"Project page with all of its studies shown.","lightbox":true}],"$Lf"]}]]}]}],"$L10","$L11","$L12"]}]
